      • TymeacParm

        public TymeacParm(java.lang.Object c_in,
          java.lang.String c_func,
          int c_interval,
          int c_millis,
          int c_pri)
        Constructor 2, with interval addition in milliseconds. For a syncRequest() the c_millis field is added to the c_interval field (* 1000) to determine the maximum time in milliseconds the reqeust will wait for all queues to finish processing.
        c_in is the input for the function.
        c_func is the Tymeac Function.
        c_interval is the interval in seconds to wait for a reply.
        c_millis is the interval in milliseconds to wait for a reply.
        c_pri is the priority for the request.

        c_func - java.lang.String
        c_interval - int
        c_millis - int
